  "text": "Since zξ is O(µξ 2 ) due to H p ,z µ = 0, z 2 is O(µ 2 ξ 2 ) for the same reason, and |η| 2 and ∂ µ |η| 2 are O(µξ 2 ) due to p ,z = 0, we deduce that H p ,z ξ < 0 for sufficiently small |µ|, so (3.31) implies (3.30). Thus, µ can be used for gluing constructions as in [CITATION_1] . 3.5. Complex absorption. The final step of fitting P σ into our general microlocal framework is moving the problem to a compact manifold, and adding a complex absorbing second order operator. We thus consider a compact manifold without boundary X for which X µ0 = {µ > µ 0 }, µ 0 = −ǫ 0 < 0, with ǫ 0 > 0 as above, is identified as an open subset with smooth boundary; it is convenient to take X to be the double of X µ0 , so there are two copies of X 0,even in X.",
